reviewText: All the other reviews for this show pretty much cover the brilliant writing, direction and acting especially Elliott. Hers is such a challenging character to play convincingly but she brings so much subtle detail to every scene that you actually believe there really ARE two people in there.The main difference between this season and the first is the progression of Levering's character 'Kim'. There is a little less of the completely unlikeable antagonist in these episodes and more a case (get it?) of her rock-solid honesty shining through under any circumstances. Although she still has the emotional intelligence of a bar of soap, (she is the antagonist to Jane's protagonist remember), this second season puts her in a little more human light than the first.One strange thing about this comedy/drama in general though is that Cho, the only stand-up comic in the whole cast, has probably the least funniest character of them all. Without a doubt, Bowlby as Stacy is the show stealer for any scene she is in. The chemistry and comedic interplay between her and Elliott is undeniable and like one of those magic pairings that can make a break a series. In this case, they make it big time.5 stars!

reviewText: Drop Dead Diva is a fairly short show, containing just 13 episodes per season. However, each episode has been solid, delivering a compelling story in the courtroom AND in Deb/Jane's personal life. Deb/Jane is still struggling with her personal life and relationship with Grayson, and there were times where I wanted to scream, 'Just tell him the truth, Deb!'The legal stories are very fun and creative, with unexpected twists and clues in the cases, making the courtroom scenes as much fun to watch as the personal drama. And the finale for this season... oh wow!

reviewText: Season 2 is overflowing with even more of the sassy humor and heart felt moments that made season 1 a hit. While season 1 had a slow start season 2 delivers one "can't miss episode" after another.I know it's silly but this show is better than ice cream at perking me up a bad day; I forget my problems and end the day feeling warm, fuzzy, and hopeful.My only complaint is that it's only 13 episodes. It feels like I have to wait forever for the new season and then the season is over right after it begins.

reviewText: The funny part is that I usually like nothing.  Well, almost nothing.  That's why I don't bother with TV.  But I find this series so much fun and original, with so many positive aspects (good acting, writing, sets, music, casting, etc.)  One thing I can't figure out and I smile at myself for trying to...Why does she get the attributes of both characters?  In other words, if Jane died, her  intelligence, personality, knowledge, etc. would have also.  But Deb gets the benefit of both women?I don't remember many series where the second season was even better than the first.  I so enjoy the wit, humor, contemporary plot lines that have imagination and creativity, and so much more.  It's a lot of fun to watch.
